.nh
.TH "SYMAIRA" "1" "May 2026" "Symaira Vault" "OpenPass Manual"

.SH NAME
symaira-agent-upgrade - Upgrade an agent's security tier


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBsymaira agent upgrade  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Show tier diff and upgrade an agent's security tier with interactive confirmation.

.PP
The upgrade applies the named tier preset (safe, standard, or admin) to the
agent profile, updating all capability fields. The legacy alias "read-only"
is accepted as a synonym for "safe". Use --dry-run to preview changes without
writing. Use --rotate-token to also rotate the agent's MCP token.

.PP
The --reason flag is required when using --yes for non-interactive mode to ensure
an audit trail.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--dry-run\fP[=false]
	Show diff without applying changes

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for upgrade

.PP
\fB--reason\fP=""
	Audit reason for the upgrade (required with --yes)

.PP
\fB--rotate-token\fP[=false]
	Rotate the agent's MCP token on upgrade

.PP
\fB--tier\fP=""
	Target security tier (safe, standard, admin; 'read-only' accepted as alias for 'safe')

.PP
\fB--yes\fP[=false]
	Non-interactive mode (requires --reason)


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--color\fP="auto"
	When to emit ANSI color: auto, always, never

.PP
\fB--no-pipe-warning\fP[=false]
	suppress 'reading from non-TTY' warning when piping secrets

.PP
\fB--output\fP="text"
	Output format (text, json, yaml)

.PP
\fB--profile\fP=""
	use a named vault profile

.PP
\fB--quiet\fP[=false]
	suppress non-error output

.PP
\fB--theme\fP=""
	Color preset: default, highcontrast, colorblind (or OPENPASS_THEME)

.PP
\fB--vault\fP="~/.openpass"
	path to the password vault


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  # Interactive upgrade to admin tier with token rotation
  openpass agent upgrade hermes --tier admin --rotate-token

  # Dry-run: preview changes without writing
  openpass agent upgrade claude-code --tier admin --dry-run

  # Non-interactive upgrade with audit reason
  openpass agent upgrade opencode --tier standard --yes --reason "CI pipeline automation upgrade"
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBsymaira-agent(1)\fP
